    "This may hinder their performance in domains such as HVAC control, where data collection is slow, as detailed in Biemann et al. (2021).",
    "This is an assumption that we will empirically test in our experiments.",
    "On the other hand, we have off-policy algorithms such as TD3 and SAC, which are more sample-efficient and can therefore be expected to produce better results in the HVAC control problem.",
    "Off-policy algorithms are based on two policies: a behaviour policy, which is exploratory, and a target policy, which is the one actually used by the agent and is based on the knowledge gathered by the exploratory one.",
    "Thus, while TD3 is an improved version of DDPG commonly used in HVAC control (Li et al. 2019; Gao et al. 2020; Biemann et al. 2021; Fu and Zhang 2021), SAC offers a promising alternative in this domain, as shown by recent studies such as (Brandi et al. 2022; Yu et al. 2020; Biemann et al. 2021; Coraci et al. 2021)."
